name: Jalen Thompson
desc: Coach Kliff Kingsbury said Friday that Thompson (ankle) aggravated the same ankle injury that landed him on injured reserve earlier this season in Thursday's loss to Seattle, Kyle Odegard of the Cardinals' official site reports.

name: Kyler Murray
desc: Murray suffered an AC joint injury in his throwing shoulder during Thursday's loss to Seattle, but the Cardinals expect him to be fine for their next game, a Week 12 matchup with the Patriots on Nov. 29, NFL Network's Ian Rapoport reports.

name: Julio Jones
desc: Interim coach Raheem Morris said Monday that Jones (hamstring) could be a "game-time decision" Week 12, William McFadden of the Falcons' official site reports.

name: Mykal Walker
desc: Walker (hamstring) is questionable to return to Sunday's matchup against New Orleans.

name: J.K. Dobbins
desc: Dobbins (illness) will be placed on the reserve/COVID-19 list after testing positive Monday, Mike Garafolo of NFL Network reports.

name: Mark Ingram II
desc: Ingram tested positive for COVID-19 on Monday and will be placed on the reserve/COVID-19 list, Mike Garafolo of NFL Network reports.

name: John Brown
desc: Coach Sean McDermott said Monday that Brown tweaked his ankle during Sunday's 32-30 loss to the Cardinals, Maddy Glab of the Bills' official site reports.

name: AJ Epenesa
desc: Epenesa was ruled out for the rest of Sunday's game versus the Cardinals after suffering a concussion.

name: Christian McCaffrey
desc: Coach Matt Rhule said Monday that McCaffrey is "week to week" ahead of the Week 12 matchup against Minnesota, Joe Person of The Athletic reports.

name: Teddy Bridgewater

name: Dennis Daley

name: Eddie Jackson

name: David Montgomery

name: Mitchell Trubisky

name: Nick Foles

name: Akiem Hicks

name: Joe Burrow

name: Denzel Ward

name: Blake Bell

name: Anthony Brown

name: Trey Marshall
